## Reading order for agents

Read in this order when joining a task. Each file has a specific job — don't skip:

1. **`docs/spec/GOLDEN_PRINCIPLES.md`** — mechanical rules (`GP-NNN`). Reference by ID in commits and dispatches.
2. **`docs/spec/ARCHITECTURE.md`** — system design and data flow.
3. **`docs/spec/LAYERS.md`** — canonical dependency direction (enforced by `GP-006` and `/check-layers`).
4. **`docs/spec/CONVENTIONS.md`** — naming, error handling, testing patterns.
5. **`docs/spec/API.md`** — endpoint contracts.
6. **`docs/spec/AGENT_DISPATCH.md`** — the five-field dispatch spec for `/implement`, `/refactor`, `/fix-bug`.
7. **`docs/spec/SMOKE_TEST.md`** — browser-test playbook for `/verify-ui`.
8. **`docs/plan/FEATURES.md`** + **`docs/plan/ACTIVE.md`** — what to build and what's in flight.
9. **`docs/plan/DECISIONS.md`** + **`docs/plan/DEPENDENCIES.md`** — accepted decisions and change-impact.
10. **`docs/plan/discovery/F-XXX-*.md`** — feature-specific design discovery, when working on F-XXX.

