## Commands

| Command | When to use |
|---------|-------------|
| `/implement F-XXX` | New feature end-to-end (plan → TDD → agents → smoke test) |
| `/fix-bug B-XXX` | Bug fix (reproduce → failing test → fix → verify) |
| `/refactor [desc]` | Refactoring (analyze → TDD → agents → verify) |
| `/garbage-collect` | Scan for Golden Principle drift, propose targeted cleanup |
| `/check-layers` | Verify dependency direction matches `docs/spec/LAYERS.md` |
| `/verify-ui [flow]` | Browser smoke test via chrome-devtools MCP |
| `/review` | Pre-PR code review (consults GP, security, perf, a11y) |
| `/test [component]` | Generate tests for a component |
| `/clean-up` | Code-quality review of the current diff, applies GP auto-fix hints |
| `/spec [file]` | Generate or update spec files |
| `/status`, `/plan` | Project dashboards |
| `/feature [cmd]`, `/bug [cmd]`, `/task [cmd]` | Backlog management |
| `/commit-push-pr` | Git workflow automation |
| `/next-phase` | Execute next development phase |

## Workflow pattern

All implementation follows: **Plan → TDD → Parallel Agents → Verify → Smoke Test → Commit.**

See `docs/spec/AGENT_DISPATCH.md` for the dispatch contract every step must honor. See `docs/spec/SMOKE_TEST.md` for the browser-test playbook.

